Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.40,0:00:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I'm on. It's on, right?\NIt's on. Today we're speaking on no
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.67,0:00:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,mind.\NSo So
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.43,0:00:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh what there is to say about it, I\Ncan't think of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.51,0:00:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,no mind. as she was pinning me up with\Nall these things. I thought the best way
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.32,0:00:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to become a good Christian is to be a\NBuddhist.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.80,0:00:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there's a wonderful Buddhist\Ncommunity here and a wonderful Christian
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.84,0:00:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,community. And uh I always say uh the\Nway to become a good Buddhist is to be a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.12,0:01:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,good Christian and vice versa because\Nthe essence of truth remains the same
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.44,0:01:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the ages.\NAnd um the novelty of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.11,0:01:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the lectures we give is that um\Na means of uh ascertaining truth which
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.79,0:01:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,was not before available became\Navailable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.04,0:01:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And we then had a way of going back over\Nspiritual and religious history
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.68,0:01:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,uh throughout all of time and um\Nreaffirming and discovering clarifying
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.43,0:01:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,many things. So the books that we've\Nbeen writing have to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.72,0:01:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,clarification\Nbecause spiritual reality is difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.24,0:01:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to comprehend by by the mind\Nand what's been written about it over
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.56,0:01:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the centuries has sometimes been\Nmisleading. Plus there is a great deal
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.71,0:02:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that is erroneous in what is considered\Nto be spiritual literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.88,0:02:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And we recommend that exercise where you\Ngo through your spiritual library
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.12,0:02:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and um everything makes you go strong\Nyou put in one pile. Everything makes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.95,0:02:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you go weak you put in another pile. And\Nit's quite an amazing discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.80,0:02:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of weed out the poppycock. And uh\Nwhat's the reason for that? It's because
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.31,0:02:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind just loves things that are\Nmysterious, magical,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.59,0:02:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, occult and, um, ooh, ooh, sounding.\NAnd we get trapped by that, the intrigue
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.51,0:02:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of the magical\Nand confusing the magical with the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.56,0:02:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,miraculous, two different realms.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.56,0:03:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so today uh we're really going to\Nsummarize what we've said so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.64,0:03:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The series of lectures has really been\Npreparatory to become acquainted with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of the ego and it's this and\Ntherefore to disassemble it. And we
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.00,0:03:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,started out to do so\Nthe very first lecture which we repeat
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,every time.\NI want you to become aware that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.84,0:03:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is happening spontaneously of\Nits own.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.23,0:03:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything here is spontaneously\Nbecoming what it is and is not being
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.64,0:03:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,caused by anything. There is no cause\Nwithin
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.68,0:03:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,reality.\Nthe subject of non-duality which has to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.59,0:03:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,do with no mind\Nwhich has to do with no mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.40,0:04:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nthe most basic understanding and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.79,0:04:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason it was the very first thing\Nwe spoke of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.43,0:04:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is the realization that causality itself\Nis an illusion because the entire ego is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.63,0:04:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the notion of causality.\NTo transcend the notion of causality
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.60,0:04:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,actually is quite a high comprehension\Nto transcend causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.36,0:04:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we asked about that one time. Mhm.\NThe transcendence of causality. We have
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.60,0:04:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,permission to ask this resist is over\N996 997 998
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.88,0:04:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,999.\NWow. So that would make it a little
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.52,0:05:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult, wouldn't it? Because\Nthe ego is based on the concept that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.19,0:05:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is being caused by something\Nelse
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.04,0:05:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and that nothing really can exist\Ntherefore
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.60,0:05:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is without being caused by\Nsomething else.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.88,0:05:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nwe repeat this each time because to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.68,0:05:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,merely hear this, to merely know it,\Nbegins to undo its power.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.44,0:05:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because creation\Nthat which is manifests by virtue of the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.47,0:05:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,grace by virtue of the grace of its\Nsource which is the creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.68,0:05:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The un the unmanifest\Nbecoming manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.19,0:05:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Ncreation itself
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.19,0:06:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of every of all existence.\NThere's only one power in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.16,0:06:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,sufficiently powerful\Nto account for existence itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.12,0:06:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of us comes in thinking well I came\Ninto this world due to the genes of my
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.19,0:06:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,parents and because of the whole long\Nsequence of genes is how we account for
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.96,0:06:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our present existence of the human race.\Nas you were. Creation is continuous
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.00,0:06:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,by grace. Each instant\Neverything is becoming the fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.84,0:06:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of its infinite of its potential.\NEverything is manifesting the power of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.28,0:06:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,creation by virtue of its source.\NTo acknowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.80,0:06:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,God as the source of one's existence is\Na very very powerful statement and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.84,0:06:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,already takes consciousness\Nuh leaps ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.72,0:07:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the source of power of the United\NStates Constitution
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.68,0:07:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates at 700 the highest in\Nthe world by virtue of the divinity of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.47,0:07:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,our creator. Out of that comes all\Nrights. All rights of our citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.72,0:07:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by vote, not by\Nthe power of politics, not by arm might,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.00,0:07:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,not by the\Nforce of a dictator, but by virtue of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.28,0:07:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity of our creator. That puts\Nit at 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.52,0:07:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, to try to remove the\Nacknowledgement
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.75,0:07:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is not really in the service of one's\Nown spiritual advancement or that of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.52,0:07:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,others.\NWhich brings us to one of the great
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.40,0:08:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,difficulties of mind\Nand that is you understand that mind
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.84,0:08:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,works\Non content within a certain context. So
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.03,0:08:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we can shorten this whole trip of\Ntranscending mind which we've tried to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.52,0:08:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,do throughout all these lectures by\Ndisassembling it. And then we finally
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.75,0:08:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,get to the core of something we can\Naddress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.91,0:08:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We all do letting go. We all do\Nsurrendering. We all try to become
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.44,0:08:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,um nonattached to the world. Let go of\Nversions and attractions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.51,0:08:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is sort of continuous. It's\Nalso sort of a continuous meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.08,0:08:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really a contemplation\Nand there's a borderline between
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.76,0:08:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,contemplation and meditation in which\Nyou go about through the day
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.08,0:08:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with a certain equinimity because as\Neach thing comes up, you let it go. As
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.12,0:09:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes up, you let it go. As you as it\Ncomes up, you let it go. And just as we
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.88,0:09:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,were leaving this morning, the kitty was\Nmissing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.51,0:09:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready to go. And the kitty's missing.\NThe screen is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is kitty?\NOh god.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.51,0:09:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's interesting what the mind does\Nat that moment. You know, it instantly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.00,0:09:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,detachs from this kitty. All kitties are\Nkittiness and let go for kittiness will
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,represent itself. And so I said to\NSusan, I I affirm the positive. Not that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.88,0:09:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he's lost, but kitty always returns.\NKitty always returns, which is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.56,0:10:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And so she called Brock and said,\N"Kitty's missing." So Brock went, he
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.68,0:10:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,lives right near us. Brock went to his\Nfront door and the kitty walked in. I
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.76,0:10:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,mean, is there a problem?\NWhat is the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.04,0:10:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitty had no problem. Sat down and purr\Nand fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.24,0:10:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that presents itself to mind,\Neverything that every little tool of the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.12,0:10:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,mind, every mechanism of the mind, we're\Ndealing with content within context.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.60,0:10:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To see all things as content\Nwithin usually an unstated context
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.32,0:10:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is one way to quickly transcend mind.\NMind focuses on content.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.00,0:11:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The content is a statement, a fact.\NKitty is missing,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.68,0:11:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever. The content then triggers all\Nkinds of emotional reactions. As you can
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.88,0:11:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,see, how can we go without kitty? I\Nmean, what might happen to kitty? The
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.72,0:11:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,dog might get kitty. The raccoon might\Nget kitty. I went outside. Sure enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.92,0:11:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a big raccoon out there. Skunks\Nall over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Coyotes who will eat kitties.\NDogs. I mean, what are we living in a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.44,0:11:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,zoo here? What is this? Wildlife zoo.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.60,0:11:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only thing you can do is\Nsurrender kitty who is the content
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.27,0:11:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to God who is the infinite context\Nand you formalize it by asking the Holy
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.64,0:11:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirit\Nto find Kitty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.00,0:12:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy Spirit was pretty quick this\Nmorning. Couple of minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.16,0:12:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly dissolving content into\Ncontext. All right. You'll see that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.12,0:12:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,almost all human error, 90% of human\Nerror, is the failure to define context.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.68,0:12:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Every night on TV, we see,\Nyou know, rather shocking examples of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.95,0:12:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,literally looking at content and\Ncompletely ignoring context
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.60,0:12:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because the truth of content depends\Ncompletely on context.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.48,0:12:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, without context, content has no\Nmeaning at all. cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.51,0:12:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night on television, there's some\Nwoman who was a abysmally abused in the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.20,0:12:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,airport going through the examination\Nline. And night after night, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.24,0:12:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,some poor creature there who's had her\Nwooden leg removed and stripped naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.12,0:12:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nnight after night, there's an atrocity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.63,0:13:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Atrocities are committed by these people\Nwho check you out at the count of the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.95,0:13:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,check-in counter. totally missing the\Nwhole point, isn't it? I mean, the total
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.95,0:13:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,missing of the intention of the whole\Nthing is so drastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.07,0:13:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're looking for black people, you\Ndon't stop stop all the white people on
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.20,0:13:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the street, do you? You're looking for\Nwhite people, you don't stop all the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.72,0:13:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,black people on the street. If you're\Nlooking for men, you don't stop all the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.20,0:13:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,women, do you?\NAnd so we see an absurdity, an absurdity
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.68,0:13:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,where the context is totally lost\Nthat people should not be harassed
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.95,0:13:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because of their race as the intention\Nand then its application becomes the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.32,0:13:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite becomes an absurdity. You see?\NOh Lord. And
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.48,0:13:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so context transforms everything.\NWhen the fire danger is high, which it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.88,0:14:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,was at the last lecture, fire danger, we\Nhad huge fires all over Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.16,0:14:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not allowed to go camping. Not\Nallowed to go camping. You can say,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.63,0:14:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, it's my right. I pay taxes. I\Nhave a right to camp."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.12,0:14:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But the context has changed.\NExtreme fire danger. So I just cite them
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,as examples we can see every night on\Ntelevision where ignoring context you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.12,0:14:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,see the absurdity of what would\Notherwise be sensible content. Nobody
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.36,0:14:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,argues that people should not be\Ndiscriminated against by virtue of race,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.88,0:14:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,culture or whatever.\NAnd then what happens to that truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.39,0:14:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That truth then becomes actually its\Nopposite. it actually becomes its
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.32,0:14:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite.\NI feel these I think these people at the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.95,0:14:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,check-in counter are on a combined\Nprogram to destroy this thing because
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.32,0:14:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it's so absurd. So they they take it to\Nthe other extreme to try and get it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.39,0:15:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,overturned because, you know,\Nstopping every little old lady who has a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.32,0:15:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,steel pin in her hip is not the way to\Nfind
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.80,0:15:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever those elitas or whatever those\Npeople are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.72,0:15:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the way to find them actually.\NAnd uh mathematically it was uh
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.16,0:15:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered that the chances are\Ndiminished by 6,000 to one by following
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.27,0:15:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,our current check-in style uh diminishes\Nits effectiveness by 6,000%.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.88,0:15:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nif we stopped all that, our chances of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.39,0:15:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,finding a real shoe bomber would be\N6,000 times higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.56,0:15:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing is absurd, is it not?\NCan you imagine a shoe bomber and he's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.32,0:15:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,going to go to heaven and uh taking all\Nthese innocent people with him? The way
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.24,0:15:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to heaven is you wear bombs in\Nyour shoes and you blow up all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.51,0:15:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,innocent people. And there's people that\Nbuy this as truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.36,0:16:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So the extent to which truth becomes\Nmangled
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.75,0:16:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,when content is taken out of context.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.19,0:16:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible.\NAnd of course it's a big problem in our
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.36,0:16:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,current society. Maybe for 50 million\Nyears or 40 million years or whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.36,0:16:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because homo sapien is really a\Ntransitional life form.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.51,0:16:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Homo sapiion is transitional. We like to\Nlook at homo sapien as the crowning
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.39,0:16:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,glory of evolution above the monkeys and\Nall those things below us. You see? And
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.56,0:16:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,now modern man in our own fantasy,\Nmodern man is the most advanced creature
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.44,0:16:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that could be really\Nwill soon be going to the moon. No, we
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.48,0:16:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,went to the moon. We still be going. No,\Nwe're going to Jupiter. So, we're going
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.68,0:16:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,someplace always to show the advancing\Nsuperiority of the human race. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.56,0:17:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if if what do we call current\Nman? Homo sapien, right? Homo sapiens.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.83,0:17:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah,\Nhomo sapien. We have permission to ask
