Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.27,0:32:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,very powerful\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.64,0:33:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,groups such as this one here are usually\Nquite ariodite compared to the rest of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.79,0:33:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the world. This is an extremely ariodite\Ngroup. I mean this is probably onetenth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.03,0:33:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of 1% of the world's population here or\Nless
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.96,0:33:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that gets up to the 400s and then in the\N400s becomes interested in spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.88,0:33:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,reality and begins to study it begins to\Nread all the great teachers. So
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.91,0:33:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,inspiration\Ntogether with the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.24,0:33:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then we find oursel in the 400s.\NSo the reason and logic then serves us
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.32,0:33:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,well. Serves us well. Increases our\Npower enormously.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.12,0:33:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You can manipulate with a computer, but\Nit would take 100,000 people a month to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.79,0:33:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,accomplish\Nin one second. You can accomplish a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.60,0:33:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,greater amount of work in one split\Nsecond than uh a large percentage of a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.60,0:33:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,whole subcontinent. If they worked all\Nday, hell every day couldn't accomplish
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.91,0:34:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,what you can accomplish because symbols\Nnow become the great power.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.84,0:34:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So reason and logic which is in the\N400s, the 400s are very very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.32,0:34:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They dominate the world right now. They\Ndominate civilized society.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.00,0:34:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The 400s which then\Ngive you the intelligence to begin to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.00,0:34:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,see the truth of spiritual realities,\Nthe capacity to read and the value of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.96,0:34:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual education\Nnow becomes as you get to the top of the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.04,0:34:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,400s,\Nwhat was an asset now becomes an
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.96,0:34:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,obstacle.\NThe 400's got you here and now you're
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.76,0:34:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,stuck with it. You're stuck with reason\Nand logic
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.59,0:34:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the constructions because the mind\Ntakes positionalities
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.72,0:34:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that positionality it\Nautomatically instantly creates duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.28,0:35:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So the lecture today our purpose is to\Nsee how can you transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.64,0:35:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,duality.\Nclassic pathway
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.32,0:35:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say of Zen and various types of\NBuddhism and monastic types of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.72,0:35:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,meditation are to transcend the mind\Naltogether to experience another reality
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.35,0:35:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,directly\Nand the various techniques about which
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.72,0:35:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I've written about which we've lectured\Nand which all of you have studied
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.04,0:35:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,certain realizations seem to potentiate\Nthat transformation that transcending
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.56,0:35:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the limits of the ego so that instead of\Nbeing an obstacle, it begins to serve
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.32,0:35:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you. Certain things merely to hear of\Nthem already begin to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.16,0:35:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,exhilarate one's progress.\NIf we say nothing is it's not possible
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.52,0:36:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for anything to cause anything else.\NEverything is manifesting its infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.80,0:36:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality by the grace of creation\Nwhich is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.07,0:36:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just that just that knowingness that\Nthought is already powerfully
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.40,0:36:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,transformative. Let's see what the\Ncalibration of that thought is. I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.00,0:36:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,know\Nhas just spoken. We have permission is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.80,0:36:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,just that is over 800 850 900 920.\NOkay. The thought has the power at 920.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.48,0:36:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the level of truth of the\Nthought. To merely hold it in mind then
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.96,0:36:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and to give it a certain reverence which\Nwe give to all truth
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.44,0:36:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then empowers that thought which then\Nsort of goes through your mind and
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.44,0:36:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,cuts off a whole bunch of circuits.\NSee what I mean? You you like let it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.44,0:36:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,loose in this\Nsincial nightmare we call the brain. And
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.28,0:37:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it runs around on its own now and begins\Nto disconnect switches.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.40,0:37:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if causality is not what\Naccounts for
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.48,0:37:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is\Nthen the mind automatically increases,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.59,0:37:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,expands its context and begins to try to\Nsense what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.72,0:37:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All that we look at then is content.\NAs you mature spiritually, you look less
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.72,0:37:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and less at content and look more and\Nmore at context.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.04,0:37:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,One begins to sense the field in which\Nthat thought is occurring.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.11,0:37:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Again you see as you expand context the\Ncontext itself is limited by certain
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.48,0:37:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,definitions and you start letting go the\Ndefinitions
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.11,0:38:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually context becomes\Nthe infinite presence out of which
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.24,0:38:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,entire universe manifest\Nthe unmanifest manifesting itself as the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.76,0:38:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,manifest which is the source of creation\Nin which we experience existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.00,0:38:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The only possible source of existence is\Ndivinity itself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.83,0:38:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of this awareness\Nand moving up into the heart where you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.32,0:38:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to see the beauty of all that\Nexists because you stop thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.92,0:38:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it. When you stop thinking about it, you\Nsee the beauty of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.20,0:38:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So through the doorway of beauty\Nand the letting go of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.40,0:38:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Nyou're branching out your awareness to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.00,0:39:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the field instead of the content of the\Nfield. One experiences the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.88,0:39:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of divinity which manifests\Nitself as existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.80,0:39:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing has the power to bring\Nabout existence from nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.07,0:39:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you take away causality as an\Nexcuse, a rationalization,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.52,0:39:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,causality is the ego's last\Nhold.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.92,0:39:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The e the Buddha defined it as the law\Nof dependent causation or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.07,0:39:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And that law is at 996.\NWhat we're talking about today
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.96,0:39:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 998.\NNothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.44,0:39:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is being continuously sourced\Nby a continuous presence which gives it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.28,0:40:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the power to manifest its infinite\Npotentiality as that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.04,0:40:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So the hummingbird\Nas his wings go down does not cause the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.16,0:40:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,next thing of his wings going up which\Ndoes not cause the next thing of this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.83,0:40:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,wing going up.\NThe source of this wing movement is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.72,0:40:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly the source of this wing movement\Nis exactly the source. It is a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.24,0:40:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,continuous source. And what the source\Ndoes is empower the potentiality to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.11,0:40:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,become manifest\Nas existence
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.83,0:40:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which we then witness as life.\NIs that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.35,0:40:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course it's clear.\NEverybody here gets it and understands
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.92,0:40:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it\Nthere. Some people don't realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.88,0:40:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they understand it. That's all. And I\Nwant to remove that obstacle. Everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.68,0:41:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,here knows that or you couldn't exist.\NHow could you exist unless you came into
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.20,0:41:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,existence? I mean, it's a stupid\Nquestion, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.11,0:41:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of existence obviously is how\Ncome you exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.11,0:41:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's a kindergarten thinking and too
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.92,0:41:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,much for advanced intellectual people\Nlike us to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.07,0:41:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The only way you can be here is\Nbecause you are here. Oh wow. Let's see
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.56,0:41:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,if that's a good one, Susie.\NLet's
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.04,0:41:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,see that is over 9989.\NOkay. So that is what they need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.44,0:41:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So that knowingness is\Npresent within you. Latent but after
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.80,0:41:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,this morning no longer latent. It's\Nvibrating in everybody's aura right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.68,0:42:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So that knowingness is there forever.\NWell, that should take care of this
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.52,0:42:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,morning's lecture, folks. Bye.\NThe pathway of duality then is is called
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.28,0:42:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,no mind.\NNo mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.52,0:42:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Um in this experience which occurred\Nwithin
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.48,0:42:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it wasn't called no mind because there\Nwas no mind mind to call it no mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.68,0:42:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned about no mind many years\Nlater.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.83,0:42:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to reacquire mind is a project.\NIt is not easy. And uh most people who
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.88,0:42:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have any mind left uh leave it\Nthat way and we don't hear from them
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.80,0:42:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,again\Nwhich is frankly the best advice. I
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.76,0:43:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,think\Nthe best thing to do when you go into a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.31,0:43:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,blitz state and realize that love God\Noneness and that which you are are one
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.80,0:43:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're immobilized in that state.\NResist the temptation to reactivate the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.83,0:43:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,body. That is my advice.\NHowever, you may have had a prior karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.80,0:43:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment about it, but which may pull\Nyou back in, but
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.04,0:43:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so the condition of no mind.\NSomebody was asking me this week, yes, I
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.20,0:43:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,want to answer some of the questions\Nthat came up in the office this week. Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.88,0:43:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,h\Nsomebody said um
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.20,0:43:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,what did he say about no mind? I can't\Nremember what he said about no mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.40,0:43:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes,\Nit was a funny question. Uh if it's the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.52,0:44:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,silence that teaches, then how can you\Nteach silence when you're talking? Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.11,0:44:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, this had to do with an interview\Nwith Ramano Maharshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.52,0:44:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,uh but Marshie in response to a question\Nhad said
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.52,0:44:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that the teaching happens as a matter of\Nsilence.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.11,0:44:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So this person wanted to know how that\Ncould be.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.83,0:44:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the silence is always\Npresent.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.76,0:44:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The talkingness does not eliminate the\Nsilence. It distracts you from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.11,0:44:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But the silence of the energy of the\Nfield itself transmits.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.16,0:44:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone within this room is sharing\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.92,0:44:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with we're all sharing it with each\Nother because we're all just one. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.07,0:44:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the oneness of that knowingness\Nis sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.40,0:44:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So while Raman Maharshi is chattering to\Nyou about something because he's got to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.00,0:45:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,amuse this visitor because visitors are\Nvery verbal. He's got to say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.20,0:45:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy came all the way from Cleveland\Nto see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.07,0:45:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So Ramana looks at him and he's busy\Neating his porridge on his palm leaf or
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.96,0:45:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,something and uh that was the\Ntransmission. Then the seeker says mama
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.92,0:45:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and Ramana says yeah yeah. So the goes\Naway feeling happy. He said this Roman
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.31,0:45:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,said that but that had nothing to do\Nwith what happened. Huh? See,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.20,0:45:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so no mind then is silent.\NNo mind is really nothing but the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.96,0:45:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,realization of the ultimate context of\None's own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.35,0:45:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nthe content the content then is your
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.56,0:45:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.\NWe said that there's content meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.88,0:45:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out of content but only only\Nwithin a context.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.68,0:46:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So then let's take as a proposition for\Nthe content your own existence
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.04,0:46:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nwhat is the ultimate context of your own
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.07,0:46:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,existence. Huh?\NI don't agree with u Mari came up
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.92,0:46:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,questions in the office. I saw some\Nvisitor this week
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.64,0:46:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,uh because of his um\Nuh instruction to
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.83,0:46:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,ask um always continuously as a\Ncontinuous contemplation. Uh who am I? I
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.92,0:46:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,don't agree with who am I\Nbecause who makes you look for a pronoun
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.31,0:46:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,looks for\Nyou see it's already a limitation. A who
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.64,0:46:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is a limitation. So, you're looking for\Na who, you know, and there ain't any who
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.16,0:47:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,ain't a who there. And you're looking\Nfor a not who.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.88,0:47:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're looking for a not who. You find a\Nwho, that ain't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.64,0:47:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You're looking for a condition. A what.\NThe sense of self within one within
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.07,0:47:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is a whatness. It's an isness. It's a\Ncondition.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.11,0:47:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's also\Nthe most powerful sense of I that can
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.92,0:47:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,exist.\NIt is I. But beyond the pronoun I. So
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.40,0:47:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm always afraid if people say, "Who am\NI?" They're looking for a pronoun. A
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.96,0:47:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,pronoun, a self-def.\NAnd it's going to take them right back
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.28,0:47:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,into the ego's definition of who you\Nthink you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.59,0:47:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite stillness behind Whatever\Nsounds we hear in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.07,0:47:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is yourself.\NWithout the infinite stillness of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.31,0:48:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself, you wouldn't be able to hear\Nanything.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.00,0:48:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the infinite\Ncontext of nonform, you would not be
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.52,0:48:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,able to experience form.\NBecause of the voidness of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.40,0:48:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence, one experiences form,\Nexperiences existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.64,0:48:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is aware of what the mind is up to.\NSo we don't want to be scared of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.88,0:48:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We handle mind the same we did the\Nanimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.76,0:48:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We love mind\Nnot our enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.20,0:48:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,took evolution\Nbillions of years to develop this
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.28,0:49:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible\Nuh thing here
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.88,0:49:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which I know because I want to realize\Nthe presence of God now becomes an
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.88,0:49:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,obstacle.\NGot all the way to Mars and now how do
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.20,0:49:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you get off the place?\NHere we are folks
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.68,0:49:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,without this you never get to Mars. Uh,\Nwhat do you do once you get to Mars? You
